text.paragraph: Includes: History of Present Illness from this encounter

paragraph.content: Matthew Lewis is a 72-year-old female with history of left breast cancer status post-surgery in 2009, hypertension, chronic diastolic heart failure, chronic kidney disease stage III, dyslipidemia, COPD, overactive bladder, chronic vertigo, and cognitive dysfunction who present with a few complaints.

The patient is complaining that her vertigo is not controlled even though we prescribed promethazine 12.5 mg every 4-6 hour as needed. The patient states that she was still very dizzy and that is making her feel more depressed and she feels very tired, and she had to lay down because of her dizziness. The patient also stated that she has more memory issues, and she would like to see a neurologist.
She states that she knows that the Phenergan does not help her, but she believes that she wants to take it regularly for her to get up and do the kitchen activities safely.

She saw the neurologist Dr. Kim in the last year and he did the sleep study on her. She mentions that Dr. Kim does not understand her situation. She saw the Dr. Gaudier a long time ago and she reports that he did not understand why he visited him. She denies stroke, seizures, Tourette's syndrome, Parkinson disease. She Know that she has cognitive issue. She does not have a problem seeing Dr. Gaudier.
Orthostatic vital sign was obtained and is negative for orthostatic hypotension.
Matthew Lewis is a 73 year old female.
